External knowledge used:
- "identities" refers to the unique identifiers of the reports (report_id);
- "popularity" refers to the number of views for each report;
- "birthdates" refers to the creation dates of the reports (created_at);
- "newest additions" refers to the top 5 most recently created reports (ranked by created_at in descending order).

sql:
SELECT reports.title, reports.report_number, reports.status, reports.created_at, departments.department_name
FROM reports
INNER JOIN departments ON reports.department_id = departments.department_id;

SELECT reports.report_id, reports.title, report_metrics.downloads
FROM reports
INNER JOIN report_metrics ON reports.report_id = report_metrics.report_id;
